FBIS4-19428 "drweu074_j_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-074 Daily Report 16 Apr 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Prime Minister Ciampi Submits Resignation Prime Minister Ciampi Submits Resignation AU1604180594 Paris AFP in English 1749 GMT 16 Apr 94 AU1604180594 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Rome, April 16 (AFP) -- Prime Minister Carlo Azeglio Ciampi handed in his resignation to President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro on Saturday [16 April], the premier's office announced. Ciampi, 73, said last week he was ready to resign after the March 27-28 general election but would do so only after the election of the speakers of the upper and lower houses of parliament. Politicians from the right-wing Freedom Alliance [Carlo Scognamiglio and Irene Pivetti respectively] were voted into the posts earlier Saturday.
